    "Komal Re + tivra Ma + komal Dha create chromatic complexity",
    "best in mid-tempo fusion to retain character",
    "Keep both Ma flavors clearly separated in sound design (e.g., distinct timbres/registrations) so the 'two Madhyams' color stays readable.",
    "Avoid busy harmonic modulation; Purvi is strongest when tension is sustained, not constantly re-resolved.",
    "If you must go rhythmic, keep melodic phrasing slow enough that the altered tones register as intention, not 'wrong notes'."
